 :tx/rationale "Set t-88751f73 title=ATT-3-IMPL: Task-conditioned relevance scoring via spec namespace overlap. When an agent has an active in-progress task tracing to spec namespace X, context blocks related to X should score higher (more relevant to the current work). APPROACH: (1) In compute_routing_from_store (routing.rs), find active tasks (status=in-progress). Extract their spec-ref namespaces using extract_criterion_identifiers. (2) Build active_namespaces: BTreeSet of namespace strings. (3) In methodology_context_blocks (context.rs), when scoring each block, compute namespace overlap: does the block's content reference any spec element in active_namespaces? If yes, relevance = 1.0. If partial overlap, relevance = 0.5 + 0.5 * overlap_fraction. If no overlap, relevance = 0.3 (baseline). (4) The relevance factor feeds into AcquisitionScore::from_factors as the relevance parameter. (5) Pass active_namespaces to methodology_context_blocks via a new parameter. ACCEPTANCE: (A) With no active tasks, all blocks get relevance=1.0 (default, not penalized). (B) With active task tracing to INV-STORE-*, store-related blocks get relevance=1.0, unrelated blocks get 0.3. (C) Relevance scoring is deterministic for same store state. (D) Multiple active tasks union their namespaces. DEPENDS-ON: ACP-SCORE-1. TRACES: INV-ATTENTION-005, ADR-FOUNDATION-024. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/routing.rs + context.rs"
